	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Mar 6th 2:45 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>This is in response to disarm traps, it's actually quite a nessecary skill.&nbsp;&nbsp;In Velketors Labyrinth (sp?) and I'm sure in other zones as well that I can't quite come up with off the top of my head there are traps that cancel magic, major pain in the butt, especially if your whole guild had to walk though them and then rebuff.  Especially the mana but also the cost on peridots from having to redo symbols/aegolism on everyone, however easily avoidable enough if the rogue has a decent skill in sense/disarm traps.  I dont know the level required but at 200 sense traps and 150 disarm traps I haven't come across a trap yet I couldn't sense and disarm.  Best way to work up that skill is using sneak/hide go to sol a and sit at the swinging blade thingee and just click it over and over and over...  However I wouldnt' worry about doing that until late 40s early 50s levels.<br><br>just my 2cp<br>&nbsp;<br>~Tactikal Mizkalculation~&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>Level 58 Rogue<br>Cruxor Thunderblade<br>Level 51 gimp Paladin<br>Vazaelle<br>Forsaken Unity ... Guildfu.com</td></tr>
